id: pm-gmnh
title: "pm health ok:false for normal telemetry queue draining is non-actionable noise"
description: "Health reports ok=false with warning 'telemetry_queue_pending:N' whenever there are queued telemetry events waiting for retry. This causes agents checking ok=true for a healthy tracker to always see false during normal operation. The pending queue is transient and self-healing; it should not flip overall health to false unless flush has been failing for an extended period (e.g., >1h or >X attempts)."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[4]: agents,health,telemetry,ux
